## Task 3 Evidence Acquisition

Objective: Learn secure evidence collection practices.
Key Practices:
- Proper Authorization: Obtain legal approval before collecting data; unauthorized evidence may be inadmissible.
- Chain of Custody: Maintain a formal document tracking evidence description, collector, date/time, storage, and access records. Ensures integrity and accountability.
- Use of Write Blockers: Prevent accidental modification of evidence when connecting suspect devices to forensic workstations. Write blockers preserve original timestamps and file states.

